
Amid the Gulf Coast's struggle to dry out and clean up, the impact of Hurricanes Katrina and Rita on state budgets has started to come into focus -- and it looks yet again as if Louisiana will take the fiercest beating. Preliminary estimates of lost tax revenue in Louisiana range from $1 billion to $3 billion, according to a Congressional Budget Office report. It predicts no long-term significant revenue losses in Alabama, Mississippi or Texas.

